    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-29T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="699"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E. W./9–2944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-29T22:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 29, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 30—2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3725. ReDepts 2232, September 18, 8 p.m. The British Ambassador having approached
                    the Soviet Government on the subject of the proposed declarations by Rumania,
                    Bulgaria and Hungary concerning the protection of refugees, I have informed
                    Molotov by letter <pb facs="1176" n="1162" xml:id="pg_1162"/> that the United
                    States Government is in agreement with the purpose of the British proposal and
                    has no objection to the suggested text of the declaration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
